---
import Site from "../../layouts/Site.astro";
const title = "Tulaa — Privacy Policy (v1.0)";
const description =
    "Tulaa Privacy Policy — local-only logs, optional anonymous analytics with PostHog, no PII.";
const effective = "2025-09-16";
---

<Site title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/legal/privacy">
    <main style="max-width:840px;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;">
        <h1 style="margin:12px 0 8px;">
            <img
                src="https://images.tulaa.life/logo.webp"
                alt="Tulaa logo"
                width="48"
                height="48"
                style="vertical-align:middle;border-radius:8px;margin-right:6px;"
            />
            Tulaa — Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="meta" style="color:#6b6b76;">
            Version 1.0 · Effective <time datetime={effective}>{effective}</time
            >
        </p>

        <div
            style="background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--ring);padding:16px 18px;border-radius:14px;"
        >
            <p>
                <strong>Short version:</strong> Your logs stay on your device. Analytics
                and crash reports are off by default. With your consent, anonymous
                crash logs (Sentry) and event analytics (PostHog) help us improve
                stability and features — never your journals or period data. No ads.
                No personal data.
            </p>
        </div>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">1) What We Collect</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>By default:</strong> nothing leaves your device.</li>
            <li>
                <strong>If you opt in:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Anonymous analytics with PostHog (feature usage events,
                        basic device info — never personal notes).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Anonymous crash reports with Sentry (technical details
                        like device model, OS, and stack traces — never your
                        personal health logs).
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">2) What Stays on Your Device</h2>
        <p>
            Yoga logs, water logs, moments/journals, rhythms, and period data.
            Private to your device unless you export/share them.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">3) How We Use Data</h2>
        <p>
            To improve stability (via crash reports) and features (via
            analytics). Both are optional, anonymous, and only used to
            understand general usage patterns. Never for advertising, profiling,
            or resale.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">4) Permissions</h2>
        <p>
            Notifications are used only if you set up Rhythms. No access to
            contacts, camera, or location.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">5) Third Parties</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <a
                    href="https://sentry.io/privacy"
                    rel="nofollow noopener"
                    target="_blank">Sentry</a
                > — error/crash reporting
            </li>
            <li>
                <a
                    href="https://posthog.com/privacy"
                    rel="nofollow noopener"
                    target="_blank">PostHog</a
                > — anonymous, opt-in product analytics
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">6) Retention</h2>
        <p>
            Your local data stays until you delete it or uninstall the app.
            Crash logs are typically retained by Sentry for ~90 days. PostHog
            analytics events are retained only as long as needed for product
            improvement (typically up to 90 days).
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">7) Security</h2>
        <p>
            Local data is sandboxed. Cached media may be encrypted at rest. We
            don’t store or transmit personal identifiers.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">8) Children</h2>
        <p>
            Not intended for children under 16. Teens 16–18 may use with
            parental guidance.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">9) Your Controls</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Export your data any time.</li>
            <li>Delete local data any time.</li>
            <li>Toggle analytics and crash reports on/off any time.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">10) Changes</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this policy. You’ll see a notice in the app when we
            do.
        </p>

        <p class="meta" style="color:#6b6b76;">
            <a href="/legal/terms">Terms of Use</a> · Need help?
            <a href="mailto:contact@tulaalife.com">contact@tulaalife.com</a>
        </p>

        <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
            {
                "@context": "https://schema.org",
                "@type": "WebPage",
                "name": "Tulaa — Privacy Policy",
                "url": "https://tulaalife.com/legal/privacy",
                "inLanguage": "en",
                "datePublished": "2025-09-16",
                "isPartOf": {
                    "@type": "WebSite",
                    "name": "Tulaa",
                    "url": "https://tulaalife.com"
                }
            }
        </script>
    </main>
</Site>
